•   { true } n,y,x:= 0,F,G { inv.n.y.x }

(1) F = ? // F = 0

(2) G = ? // G = 1

≡   Hoare triple

    true ⇒ wp.(n,y,x:= 0,F,G).(inv.n.y.x)

≡   Left identity of ⇒

    wp.(n,y,x:= 0,F,G).(inv.n.y.x)

≡   Assignment

    (inv.n.y.x)[n,y,x:= 0,F,G]

≡   Definition of inv; λ comp

    •   0,F,G ≥ 0 // 0,0,1 ≥ 0
    
    F = f.0 ∧ G = f.(0+1)

≡   Arithmetic

    F = f.0 ∧ G = f.1

≡   Definition of f, twice

    F = 0 ∧ G = 1   -- Assumptions (1,2)

■